cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DM, cs.SE 

This paper discusses the performance of a machine learning technique, Genetic Programming (GP), in the presence of noisy data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also uses synthetic datasets, which could fall under cs.DM (Data Mining) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
